string.name: emc_rescue_disclaimer_content_part_1
string.value: [TS_1122973]_The emergency rescue signals that this feature searches for are transmitted by specialized rescue teams, such as fire departments, using specialized equipment.  has no control over these rescue signals, nor can it guarantee that rescue teams will travel to your location to provide rescue services.

string.name: emc_rescue_disclaimer_content_part_2
string.value: [TS_1122974]_The off-grid emergency communication feature is intended solely as a reference to aid you in assessing safety risks and making safety decisions. This feature is only used to search for rescue signals, and does not actively send out distress signals. Enabling this feature does not guarantee that rescue teams will come to your aid. Rescue signals are transmitted by rescue teams using specialized equipment. If your device does not detect a rescue signal, it is your responsibility to take appropriate safety measures based on your situation. If your device detects a rescue signal, you should accurately report your situation to rescue personnel. You should take reasonable measures to stay safe based on your current environment, both before and after rescue teams contact you. You shall bear sole responsibility for any risks or consequences that may arise from any course of action you take based on the off-grid emergency communication feature.

string.name: emc_rescue_disclaimer_content_part_3
string.value: [TS_1122972] shall not assume liability for any losses that may be incurred if your device does not receive rescue signals, or you do not receive aid, owing to factors such as terrain, buildings, and weather, or due to other force majeure events.
